Program: Outlook
Title: 12/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00sz6g1
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 13 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, with renewed violence in western Burma between Buddhists and Muslims - or Rohingyas - we hear from a young Rohingya refugee who wants to make Malaysia her home. Also, a successful London broker describes how her cocaine addiction came to dominate her life. And beluga whale expert Olga Shpak takes us to the remote islands in the Sea of Okhotsk where she does her research. (Image: A beluga whale in Beijing Aquarium. Credit: AFP Photo / Getty Images / Mark RALSTON) Show less